<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Britain-Robbery     12-20 0230</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Britain-Robbery,0235</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bank Robber Dies In Siege After Policeman Killed In Raid</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhotos LON3,4,5</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COVENTRY, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bank robbers killed one policeman and
seriously wounded another in the central England city of Coventry
Monday before holing up in a suburban house where one robber shot
himself to death, police said.
   One of the alleged robbers gave himself up but the other ignored
police attempts to negotiate and then shot himself in the head in a
back room of the house, said West Midlands Assistant Chief Constable
Mervyn Jones.
   Police Superintendent Martin Burton said the officer who died was
an unarmed patrolman in his mid-30s. He was thought to have died
instantly after being shot at point-blank range with a
double-barreled shotgun.
   Police said he had stopped the raiders' getaway car soon after
the robbery at the Midland Bank in which $1,100 was stolen.
   The robbers then switched cars and drove onto a highway where
they were rammed by an unmarked police car. Police said a patrolman
in that vehicle was shot in the stomach.
   The gunmen then ran across a golf course before forcing their way
into the home of a plumbing contractor and his family. It was not
known whether they took any hostages.
   Police said the wounded officer, also in his 30s, was recovering
in hospital. A third officer was being treated in hospital for shock.
</TEXT>
