<2ND_LINE>PM-Germany-Escape,0107</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Two Brothers Flee to West Berlin, Guards Hold Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERLIN (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two East German brothers fled to West Berlin early
today, climbing over border barriers as Communist guards fired
flares but refrained from using their weapons, West Berlin police
said.
   The brothers, aged 28 and 26, reached a U.S. guard post unharmed
and were turned over to West Berlin police.
   The escape occurred in the southern West Berlin district of
Lichterfelde, police said.
   Nearly 500 East Germans have escaped to West Berlin or West
Germany this year, compared with 288 in all of 1987, according to
official West German figures.
