<FILEID>AP-NR-12-20-88 0946EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r w PM-BRF-Reagans-Christmas     12-20 0158</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF-Reagans-Christmas,150</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Reagans To Host Two Holiday Celebrations</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan and his wife, Nancy, will have
turkey and cranberry sauce for Christmas dinner, not once but twice
in a coast-to-coast holiday celebration.
   The Reagans are having an early Christmas dinner Thursday evening
at the White House. Their guests will be Dr. Richard Davis, the
first lady's stepbrother; his wife, Patricia; their son, Geoffrey;
their daughter and son-in-law, Mr. and Mrs. Jon Peterson; and Nancy
Reynolds, a family friend, and her son, Michael.
   On Friday, the Reagans plan to fly to Los Angeles. On Christmas
Day, they will have dinner at their new home there with the
president's daughter, Maureen, and her husband, Dennis Revell; the
president's son, Michael, and his wife, Collen; and the Reagans'
son, Ron, and his wife, Doria. The Reagans' daughter, Patti, who is
estranged from her parents, will not attend.
   Turkey and cranberries are on the menu for both dinners.
