<HEAD>Anti-Apartheid Lawyer Denied Passport</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAPE TOWN, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A prominent anti-apartheid lawyer
today said the government has refused to grant him a passport to
attend law conferences in Egypt and Venezuela.
   Omar Dullah, regional chairman of the National Association of
Democratic Lawyers and of the banned United Democratic Front, said
his passport had expired in March and the government had refused to
renew it.
