of the International Commission of Jurists.
   There was no immediate response from the Department of Home
Affairs, which as a practice does no did not comment on its
decisions regarding passports and visas.
   Under apartheid, blacks have no vote in national affairs and
whites control the economy and maintain racially segregated schools
and housing districts.
