<HEAD>Two Men, One In Santa Claus Suit, Hold Up Armored Car</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES throughout with police estimating $695,000 taken,
disgused robber holding revolver, witnesses' accounts. ADDS byline.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By MARK SEAVY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WEST HARTFORD, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man dressed in a Santa Claus suit
and brandishing a revolver robbed an armored car of $695,000 today,
then fled with an accomplice in a Volkswagen, police said.
   The robber took two sacks of cash from a Dunbar Armored Security
Inc. guard as the guard and his partner picked up the money from a
United Bank branch at a shopping plaza, said Detective Capt. Russell
Hughes. One guard was inside the bank when the robbery occurred.
   ``I was just shocked that anyone would do such a thing,'' said
Enis E. Barressi, a part-time teller at the bank.
   The disguised robber hopped into a brown Volkswagen Jetta driven
by the second man and escaped on a nearby highway, Hughes said. No
shots were fired.
   The robbery occurred shortly before 9:30 a.m.
   A witness to the robbery followed the suspects' car for about a
mile and provided police with descriptions of the robbers, said Lt.
Anthony Duffy.
   A woman who answered the telephone at Dunbar Armored Security in
New Britain acknowledged that it was a Dunbar car that was robbed.
``We are not commenting at this time,'' she said.
   An employee at the United Bank, who wouldn't give her name, said,
``I cannot reveal anything.''
