<NOTE>Eds: LEADS to UPDATE throughout with patrol correcting casualty
figures to 16 sted 22 died; no pickup.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>BOGOTA, Colombia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sixteen people were killed and 11
severely burned when an interstate bus caught fire, Colombia's
highway patrol said today.
   In a news release, the patrol said the bus had stalled and the
driver was pouring gasoline into the carburetor when the gasoline
exploded.
   Earlier, the patrol had reported 22 deaths and 12 injuries from
the accident. There was no explanation for the revision.
   The gasoline exploded inside the bus near the front door,
blocking the passengers' escape, the patrol said.
   The bus driver was the only person to escape uninjured, the
patrol said.
   The accident occurred Monday night near the town of Socha, about
140 miles northeast of Bogota.
