<HEAD>Time Man of the Year To Be Announced On CNN</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Time magazine's annual Man of the Year will be
announced Saturday afternoon in a 30-minute program on Cable News
Network.
   CNN spokeswoman Alyssa Levy said the program, which will be
broadcast initially at 4:30 p.m. EST, is being produced ``behind
locked doors.''
   ``Only about four people in the company know who it is,'' she
said. The program will be rebroadcast 2 a.m. Sunday.
   The Man of the Year issue will be on newsstands Dec. 26.
   This is the second year the Atlanta-based cable network has
announced the selection, which is made on the basis of the person or
thing editors of the news magazine feel has had the greatest impact
on the year's events.
   Soviet leader Mikhail Gorbachev was 1987's Man of the Year.
Previous winners include President Ronald Reagan, baseball
commissioner Peter Ueberroth for his work in the 1984 Summer
Olympics in Los Angeles and Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini of Iran.
