<2ND_LINE>AM-NBC Headquarters,0164</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>NBC Signs Lease To Stay in NYC</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   NBC signed a lease Tuesday that will keep its
corporate headquarters in New York at least until the year 2022.
   The company, which was wooed heavily by city officials last year
when it considered a plan to move to New Jersey, signed an agreement
with the owners of Rockefeller Center to remain in the landmark
Manhattan building where it has had its headquarters since 1933.
   NBC declined to reveal the terms of the lease, which expires in
2022 and gives the company the option to renew for three 10-year
periods, ending in 2052. A previous lease was due to expire in
September 1997.
   Mayor Edward I. Koch announced last December that NBC would
expand and renovate its quarters under an agreement in which the
city would provide up to $73 million in real estate tax breaks.
   The network employs more than 3,000 people at Rockefeller Center.
</TEXT>
