<1ST_LINE>r f PM-OilPrices     12-20 0183</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Oil Prices,0190</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Oil Futures Prices Mixed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Oil futures prices began the week on a mixed
note, with wholesale unleaded gasoline gaining more ground but the
rest of the market retreating sharply.
   On the New York Mercantile Exchange, the January contract for
unleaded gasoline settled at 45.42 cents a gallon Monday, up 0.29
cent from the close Friday, when it rose 1.48 cents. Other contract
months declined.
   Among other refined petroleum products traded on the exchange
Monday, January wholesale home heating oil fell 1.27 cents to 50.75
cents a gallon, after jumping 1.08 cents Friday.
   The January contract for West Texas Intermediate, the benchmark
grade of U.S. crude oil, settled at $16.31 a barrel, down 41 cents
from Friday. It rose 37 cents in the previous session.
   Andrew Lebow, a senior energy analyst with E.D.&F. Man
International Futures Inc., attributed Monday's price movements
largely to technical factors.
   ``I think WTI and heating oil were a bit overbought ... and
besides we're due for some warmer weather'' in the Northeast,
thereby lessening the demand for heating oil, he said.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
