<1ST_LINE>u f PM-WallStreet3pm     12-20 0356</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Wall Street 3pm,0374</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market clung to some modest gains this
afternoon, with blue-chip issues generally doing better than the
broader market.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials, which rose 21.97 points
on Monday, was up another 6.07 at 2,178.75 with one hour left in the
session.
   The blue-chip index's post-crash closing high was 2,183.50 set
Oct. 21.
   Advancing and declining issues were running about even in
nationwide trading of New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with
711 up, 715 down and 546 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 132.42 million shares at 3 p.m.
on Wall Street compared with 124.10 million shares at the same point
on Monday.
   The market appeared to take some early encouragement from a pair
of economic reports that seemed to signal low inflation and moderate
economic growth.
   The government reported the consumer price index rose 0.3 percent
in November, and lowered its estimate of economic growth in the
July-through-September period to 2.5 percent from 2.6 percent.
   The reports contributed to a rally in the credit markets, where
prices of some long-term bonds were up by as much as $8.75 for every
$1,000 in face value while interest rates pulled back.
   But analysts said profit-taking eroded some of the stock market's
early gains, and some observers warned the recent rally may be
short-lived.
   The skeptics note that short-term interest rates near 9 percent
are making Treasury issues such as one-year bills attractive
compared with the uncertain yields on stocks.
   Inco Ltd. led the list of most actively-traded issues on the
NYSE, rising 1} to 26|.
   International Business Machines was up ~ at 123|. Elsewhere in
the technology group, Digital Equipment was up [ at 95[, Hewlett
Packard was up 1| at 53[ and Honeywell was up \ at 60{.
   First Fidelity Bancorp was off 2[ at 25}. The company announced
last week it expected to lose $145 million to $190 million in the
current quarter.
   The NYSE's index of all its listed common stocks rose 0.17 to
156.55. At the American Stock Exchange, the composite market index
was up 0.84 at 299.54.
