<2ND_LINE>BC-Toyota Exports,0181</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Toyota To Begin Exporting Camrys, Corollas To Taiwan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Toyota Motor Corp.'s U.S. sales unit said Tuesday
it will begin exporting U.S.-built models to Taiwan next month.
   The automaker will export Camrys manufactured at its Georgetown,
Ky., plant and Corollas assembled in a joint venture with General
Motors Corp. in Fremont, Calif., Toyota Motor Sales U.S.A. Inc. said
in a statement from its Torrance, Calif., headquarters.
   The initial shipment to Ho Tai Motor Co. Ltd., Toyota's
distributor in Taiwan, will include 300 Camrys and 100 Corollas,
said Bob McCurry, executive vice president for Toyota Motor Sales.
   Debra Sanchez, a Toyota Motor Sales spokeswoman, said exports
would be adjusted based on market demand. She said Toyota will ship
300 Camrys a month starting in January, and 100 Corollas monthly
beginning in March.
   Toyota tested the Taiwan market in August when it shipped 200
Corolla FX models, which sold promptly, McCurry said.
   The Camry and Corolla sedans are Toyota's best selling models in
the United States, Toyota Motor Sales said.
